# Plan execution

The project is organized into phases (see
[`docs/plan/MVP_PLAN.md`](../../docs/plan/MVP_PLAN.md)), and current state is
tracked as a checklist in
[`docs/plan/progress.md`](../../docs/plan/progress.md).

## Before starting work

1. Read the current state of `progress.md`.
2. Identify the next logical task (earliest open `[ ]` or `[~]` checkpoint).
3. If the order or task is unclear, **ask the user**.

## During work

- Card content audit also updates [`docs/plan/inventory.md`](../../docs/plan/inventory.md)
  (card status, copy count, notes).
- New design decisions: see [`decision-recording.mdc`](decision-recording.mdc).
- Any change: see [`changelog-discipline.mdc`](changelog-discipline.mdc).

## After work

1. Update relevant checkpoints in `progress.md` (`[ ]` → `[~]` → `[x]`, or
   `[-]` if dropped).
2. If new work emerged during the session, add it to the appropriate phase.
3. Verify all expected side-effects (CHANGELOG, inventory, open-questions)
   were updated.

## Status markers

- `[ ]` open / not started
- `[~]` in progress
- `[x]` done
- `[-]` dropped / out of scope
